-- 
Crude Oil Volatility Rises as Futures Tumble to One-Week Low

-- B y   M a r g o t   H a b i b y
-- 
2011-09-06T17:51:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/crude-oil-volatility-rises-as-futures-tumble-to-one-week-low.html
Oil options volatility increased as
the underlying futures fell to the lowest level in more than a
week as speculation that the European debt crisis is spreading
pressured the euro and equities.  Implied volatility for at-the-money options expiring in
October, a measure of expected price swings in futures and a
gauge of options prices, was 46.7 percent at 1:34 p.m. in  New
York , up from 39.6 percent on Sept. 2.  Oil for October delivery tumbled $2.15, or 2.5 percent, to
$84.30 a barrel on the  New York Mercantile Exchange . The futures
have fallen 7.7 percent this year. Oil touched $83.20 a barrel,
the lowest intraday price since Aug. 26 on the Nymex.  Floor trading was closed yesterday for the U.S. Labor Day
holiday and electronic trades will be booked with todayâ€™s
transactions for settlement purposes.  The most active contract in electronic trading today was
October $80 puts, with 1,784 lots changing hands. The options
rose 27 cents to $1.12 a barrel. October $75 puts, the next-most
active contract, gained 8 cents to 47 cents with 1,479 lots
trading. One contract covers 1,000 barrels of crude.  Puts outnumbered calls by 53 percent to 47 percent in
electronic trading on the Nymex.  The exchange distributes real-time data for electronic
trading and releases information on floor trading, where the
bulk of options trading occur the next business day.  October $75 puts were the most active options traded in the
previous session, with 6,742 lots changing hands. They rose 10
cents to 39 cents a barrel. The next-most-active options,
October $80 puts, increased 27 cents to 85 cents a barrel on
volume of 5,041.  Open interest was highest for December $100 calls with
49,512 contracts. Next were December $70 puts with 46,454 and
December $50 puts with 43,146.  To contact the reporter on this story:
